<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 3: The Robot's Secret</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>🤖 Challenge 3: The Robot's Secret</h1>
      <p class="desc">Websites have a special file that tells search engine "robots" where NOT to go. But you're not a robot... right?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="story-box">
        This blogger thinks she hid some secret pages. She told the search engine robots to stay away — but that file is <strong>public</strong> and anyone can read it. If you figure out the file's name, you'll find the hidden page!
      </div>

      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>📝 Someone's Blog</span>
          <span>Posts | About | Contact</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Welcome to My Blog!</h2>
          <p>There are some pages I don't want anyone to find~</p>
          <p>I told the robots to stay away, so nobody will discover them... right? 😏</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠️ Quick tip</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The file is called <code>robots.txt</code> and lives at the root of every website</li>
          <li>Try adding <code>/robots.txt</code> to the URL in your browser!</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Need a hint?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Visit <code>http://localhost:3000/robots.txt</code>. See the <code>Disallow</code> path? Go to that page!</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch3')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
